# Billing: Clerk Billing

All subscription and payment logic is handled by Clerk Billing. Never use Stripe directly or implement custom billing logic.

## Plans

- `free_user` — default free tier
- `pro` — paid tier

## Features

- `3_deck_limit` — user is capped at 3 decks
- `unlimited_decks` — user can create unlimited decks
- `ai_flashcard_generation` — user can generate cards with AI

## Checking Access in Server Components / Server Actions

Use `has()` from the `auth()` object to gate access server-side:

```tsx
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'

const { has } = await auth()

// Check by plan
const isPro = has({ plan: 'pro' })

// Check by feature
const canUseAI = has({ feature: 'ai_flashcard_generation' })
const hasUnlimitedDecks = has({ feature: 'unlimited_decks' })
```

## Checking Access in Client Components

Use the `<Show>` component to conditionally render UI:

```tsx
import { Show } from '@clerk/nextjs'

// Gate by plan
<Show when={{ plan: 'pro' }} fallback={<UpgradePrompt />}>
  <ProFeature />
</Show>

// Gate by feature
<Show when={{ feature: 'ai_flashcard_generation' }} fallback={<UpgradePrompt />}>
  <AIGenerateButton />
</Show>
```

## Pricing Page

Use the `<PricingTable />` component on a dedicated `/pricing` page:

```tsx
import { PricingTable } from '@clerk/nextjs'

export default function PricingPage() {
  return (
    <div style={{ maxWidth: '800px', margin: '0 auto', padding: '0 1rem' }}>
      <PricingTable />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Rules

- Always use `has()` for server-side access checks; never trust client-passed plan/feature flags
- Use `<Show>` for client-side UI gating; never conditionally render billing-gated UI via local state
- Never write custom subscription/payment logic — Clerk Billing handles everything
